review_blob: Pours golden, clear with a light, lacey head. Aroma is malted barley, yeast slightly hoppy. Taste is not like other Grain Belt products as it has hoppy notes. Not bad for an August Schell lager.
beer_name: Grain Belt: Lock and Dam Lager

review_blob: Aromas of malt, grass and a little citrus. Pours cloudy caramel with a white head. Flavor is initially grain with malt and bitter hops. Finnish is mostly bitter hops with a little citrus. Hides its 7% ABV well. Ballanced pretty well.

Pours dark brown-caramel with light brown head. Malt and roasted coffee aromas and a little caramel. Flavor is dark chocolate, coffee, malt and caramel. Starts both sweet and bitter, balanced and smooth finish.
beer_name: Lift Bridge The Warden Milk Stout

review_blob: In 12 oz bottle. Pours dark caramel with short-lived head. Aroma of the root beer from the same company, only with the addition of a malt component. It is a malt liquor, so that makes sense. The root beer does a good job of hiding the 5% ABV. Aftertaste is more malt. Overall, if you like root beer, this will work.
beer_name: Sprecher Bootleggers Bourbon Barrel Hard Root Beer

review_blob: Pours like a pilz. Smells like a pilz. Taste is more complex and hoppy. Finish is dry and slightly bitter.
Good head. Aroma is mostly malt with chocolate. Maltn coffee and chocolate flavors that hide the 7.0 ABV well. Smooth and easily drinkable.
beer_name: Finnegans Dead Irish Poet Extra Stout

review_blob: I really like this style beer. The floral notes and grassy flavors go well with the fairly high ABV this dbl IPA packs. Plays well with the rosemary & Himalayan pink salt bread Im easting with it.

12 oz bottle, thanks Mica. Pours black with brown head. Aroma is chocolate and malt and a little spruce. Taste is bakers chocolate, caramel and resin. finish is dry with a hint of the alcohol content. Mouthfeel is medium thick with moderate carbonation.I am a fan of complicated beers. This is one.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Aluminum pounder. Pours light yellow small white head. Aroma of hops which is a good thing. Flavor is hops, citrus and floral notes. Slight bitter finnish.Fairly carbonated. Not bad for a pale lager.
Pours amber with light brown head. Aroma is grain, malt, burnt caramel. Taste is mostly malt with some hops on the finish. Not exciting , but easy to drink.

Pours cloudy yellow with a white head. Aroma is yeast, grain & buttery. Flavor of hops is there, but muted by the grain. Alcohol taste is not present. Fairly carbonated. Better that the sweeter unfiltered wheats.

The aroma, I swear I smell banana bread along with grains and rust. The taste starts with grains but is overwelmed by isopropyl alcohol and chemicals. It was not a good experience for me, but I will see how it sells.
